@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "In_And_Out" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a space next to your current position (where the
smiling face icon is located), you can move horizontally, vertically or
diagonally. If the move is possible, the game will 'teleport' you at
another position on the board.

  Every space has a specific destination, so each time you go to a tile,
you will always end at the same position on the board. At least one tile
will send you to the Exit, you just have to find which one... On some
levels, 'Mystery' tiles (tiles marked by a '?' sign) are randomly placed
on the game board, unlike the 'normal' tiles, their destination will
change; with luck, it may send you to the Exit!

  On other levels, in addition to the 'Mystery' tiles, when you click on
a tile and then get teleported, that tile may be replaced by a 'Hole'
(the octagonal shapes). When this happens, that tile becomes unusable,
so you cannot go to that tile thereafter... and beware if you get to a
space that is surrounded by these holes, in which case you are trapped
and the game is over.

  When you complete a game level, 'In_And_Out' displays some statistics,
showing how many moves you did on the current level, the total number of
moves in the game (including the last moves, if the game is over), the
level where you did the least amount of moves and an average amount of
moves made on each level.

  Have fun!

